title: For Sale:  Defensive Handgun course After the Concealed Carry Handgun (ACCH)
location: Apex NC, Raleigh / Durham / CH, North Carolina
postcontent:
June 14th @1730 (5:30pm) -(Former Student Discount Applied)
Wake County Firearms & Training Center Apex, NC

This class is designed for the person who has their CCH but has no (or little) formal handgun training. The student is carrying their handgun for personal protection and needs to hone their skills in order to improve both their familiarity and skills with their chosen pistol. The class was created with wide latitude allowing a broad range of skill levels to benefit from the class.

8 students (4 hours) Students need to be 18 years of age or older (Exceptions can be made with a parent or guardian attending)

This class is designed to teach the student the fundamentals of defensive pistol shooting.

The student is instructed in firearm safety, grip, sight alignment, stance, presentation, trigger control, target acquisition, & high and low ready position during the (1) one hour of classroom lecture. The class then moves to the indoor range for (3) three hours of live fire instruction.


Student Required to Bring:

Handgun
300-400 rounds of appropriate ammunition
Suitable holster of correct size and type (if unsure please inquire)
One (at least) spare magazine
Magazine holder
Shooting glasses
Range ears



This is a "lost brass" class. (Please choose ammunition accordingly)



The fundamentals of defensive shooting are taught from distances of (1) one to (25) yards utilizing a variety of targets. Call targets of different colors, shapes, and compositions are used in order to challenge the shooter regardless of skill level. We designed this class to give any shooter, which has completed their NC CCH, a series of exercises that will improve both skill and confidence. We designed this class to instill familiarity with the handgun. Once the student gains proficiency with the firearm he/she will no longer view the handgun with intrepidation and he/she will look forward to the range. Once the student becomes comfortable and self-assured the range time will become both enjoyable and productive. Upon completion of this class the student will no longer look at the handgun as a mystery but as a tool. When the barriers are removed the improvements in shooting ability will be prompt and natural. It is for this reason that the live fire exercises are designed to be both entertaining and fun. The student will improve her/his skills and gain a new confidence in both himself and her/his firearm of choice.

The class is kept to (8) eight students with (4) four instructors to ensure each student receives the applicable instruction. Each student is assessed and then the live fire drills are adjusted to be commensurate with the student's abilities. This course is exciting, fast paced, and above all...FUN. Upon completion of the course each student will receive a certificate of completion and an ACCH grad T-shirt.

    do NOT contact me with unsolicited services or offers

title: For Sale:  New Colt 1911A1 Commercial/Military
postcontent:
One of 6,575 unsold commercial Government Model pistols transferred by Colt to their existing Military contract (No. W-478-ORD-1528).  The GOVERNMENT MODEL inscription on the frame was removed and was restamped UNITED STATES PROPERTY in its place and M1911A1 U.S. ARMY in front of the pin for the takedown lever.   The commercial serial numbers were removed and they were renumbered in the military serial number range beginning with number 860003.  Then the guns were parkerized.

This pistol was manufactured with the Swartz Safety (which was a firing pin block safety added to Government Model pistols around 1938) but the internals have been removed upon conversion to the military contract.  This pistol also has the letter S (the commercial sale mark) stamped inside the slide and frame.  This pistol has three original commercial magazines which were also transferred to the military contract.  The are full blued, with riveted bases and are marked COLT over .45 AUTO.  The bottoms of all three magazines are parkerized.

There is a P proof on the top of the slide, in front of the rear sight and alto a P on the left side of the frame near the magazine release button.  The barrel in this gun is a commercial barrel marked COLT .45 AUTO on the left side, with the commercial sale mark S in front of the barrel lug on the underside of the chamber.  There is no P on the left lug.

Gun has Type 2 Coltwood plastic grips with strengthening ribs, mold numbers and large reinforcing rings around screw holes.

I will ship Gun to any state.... No bidding and no trading.

title: For Sale/Trade:  New Series13 MPC AR, free mods for life!
postcontent:
Hour Thirteen Defense Solutions

Modular Platform Carbine
S p e c i a l   I n t r o   P r i c e ! ! !

Free labor on all future modifications FOR LIFE!

   The "Skinny Essential" middy got us thinking, it's a great way to get into an S13 gun with fairly basic furniture, that the user can upgrade later to his/her tastes. So why not take this idea further?

   Enter the Series13 MPC System. From stem to stern, this is pure Series13. Our premium cherry-picked forged receivers ensure a solid, no-wobble fit without the need for bandaid fixes like tensioning screws or "wedge" inserts. Our unstoppable SevereDuty BCG leads out to the finest 11595E certified barrel, and all components & controls are custom fitted for silky smooth operation, every time.

   For the MPC, future mods were kept in mind. Most importantly, we wanted to retain the structural integrity of the barrel if the user decides to upgrade to a free-float fore-end. This was achieved by the use of Armalite's rock solid clamp-on A2 FSB, which eliminates the need to drill into the barrel for taper pins. Along with this, our precise "buried pin" technique of pinning/welding muzzle devices (14.5" barrels) allows us to carefully cut & drill the weld. We can remove & reinstall the M/D without damaging it or the barrel.

> Lower - Forged 7075t6, mil-spec, hardcoat anodized, typeIII
> BCG - H13 Severe-Duty
